                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13144388" author="alangates" created="Fri, 4 Nov 2011 21:57:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is that the java parameters are stored in an environment variable, PIG_OPTS.  This is not being unset when a new test is ran.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13144429" author="alangates" created="Fri, 4 Nov 2011 22:49:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did cheat a bit.  This patch also adds an hdfs temp path to the test harness so we don&apos;t have to worry about whether the bloom filters are already existing in HDFS.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13145690" author="daijy" created="Mon, 7 Nov 2011 18:44:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
